# WHAT TO BUILD\
\
## 1. Behavior-Aware Retrieval Layer\
\
Add a behavior intelligence layer on top of the existing RAG pipeline.\
\
The system should learn patterns such as:\
- which aircraft a user most frequently accesses\
- which book types they most frequently open\
- which queries they repeat often\
- which role-specific tasks they usually perform\
- which tail numbers they are assigned to\
- which document types they usually need first\
\
Examples:\
- A mechanic working mostly on Cessna 152 aircraft should get faster retrieval and smarter defaults around 152-related books, parts, entries, and maintenance records.\
- An owner managing 100 aircraft should get more dashboard/report/reporting-oriented retrieval.\
- A pilot should get operational and POH-related retrieval.\
- A CFI should get training/procedure/safety-oriented retrieval.\
- An A&P should get maintenance/manual/parts/compliance retrieval.\
- An IA should get inspection/annual/signoff/compliance-heavy retrieval.\
\
This layer should:\
- prioritize likely relevant aircraft\
- prioritize likely relevant document classes\
- pre-rank likely chunks before full retrieval\
- suggest likely follow-up actions\
- reduce unnecessary search friction\
- speed up repeated queries over time\
\
But:\
- never hide the source of truth\
- never fabricate\
- never override actual permissions\
- never replace document-grounded answers\
