## 2. Role-Aware Intelligence Profiles\
\
Implement role-aware system behavior.\
\
The same dataset should behave differently depending on the user role.\
\
### Suggested roles:\
- Owner / Admin\
- Pilot\
- CFI\
- Mechanic Helper / OJT / Assistant\
- A&P Mechanic\
- IA Mechanic\
- Inspector / Auditor\
- General Viewer\
\
### Examples of role behavior:\
- **Owner/Admin**\
  - wants summaries, fleet-level insights, maintenance status, hours, trends, aircraft-level overview, due items\
- **Pilot**\
  - wants POH, W&B, limitations, operational questions, tail-specific aircraft info\
- **CFI**\
  - wants training-related procedures, student-safe operational guidance, reference materials\
- **OJT / Helper / Assistant Mechanic**\
  - can prepare drafts but cannot sign\
  - can gather info, draft log entries, share upward to supervisor\
- **A&P**\
  - can prepare and sign standard maintenance entries within permission scope\
- **IA**\
  - can sign off annuals / inspection-authorized tasks / higher-authority entries\
- **Inspector / Auditor**\
  - wants traceability, logs, airworthiness status, compliance chains\
\
System must adapt:\
- search ranking\
- suggested actions\
- prompt defaults\
- dashboard shortcuts\
- entry generation permissions\
- signoff permissions\
- escalation recommendations\
\
