\
## 3. Permission-Aware Entry Generation\
\
The platform is chat-first. A user can ask in one box:\
- prepare a logbook entry\
- generate 100-hour entry\
- generate annual inspection entry\
- prepare discrepancy correction\
- prepare return to service statement\
\
The system must understand:\
1. what type of entry is being requested\
2. whether the user is allowed to sign it\
3. whether they can only draft it\
4. whether it must be shared to a superior\
\
### Logic rules:\
- Anyone with view access may ask for information.\
- OJT/helper/non-licensed users may draft, but cannot sign.\
- A&P may sign tasks allowed under A&P authority.\
- IA may sign annuals and inspection-authorized tasks.\
- If user lacks proper authority:\
  - generate the entry draft\
  - mark signature area disabled/greyed out\
  - show explanation: "You can prepare this draft, but you do not have permission to sign this entry."\
  - offer action: "Share with supervisor"\
- If user has authority:\
  - allow signature flow\
  - capture license number if needed\
  - validate license/role before final signoff\
- If entry type requires license metadata and it is missing:\
  - ask for required missing information before finalization\
\
---\
\
## 4. Signature Permission UI Logic\
\
Implement signature-state logic in the generated entry panel.\
\
### Signature states:\
- **enabled** = user is authorized to sign this specific type of entry\
- **disabled/greyed** = user can draft but not sign\
- **hidden** = user role should not even see sign controls\
- **pending metadata** = user may sign but required info is missing (license no., certificate data, date, etc.)\
\
### Example:\
If an OJT/helper says:\
> Generate a 100-hour entry for N12345\
\
System should:\
- generate the draft\
- show required fields if needed\
- disable signature\
- display message such as:\
  - "This entry can be drafted by you, but must be reviewed and signed by an authorized A&P or IA."\
- provide options:\
  - Share to supervisor\
  - Save as draft\
  - Request review\
\
If an A&P asks for a standard maintenance signoff:\
- allow signature if within scope\
\
If annual inspection requested:\
- only IA can finalize/sign\
\
