## 7. Retrieval Ranking Logic\
\
Build a ranking strategy that combines:\
\
- document relevance\
- aircraft match\
- role relevance\
- recent activity\
- frequent usage patterns\
- permission context\
- recency\
- exact metadata match\
- chunk/document type priority\
\
### Example scoring inputs:\
- base semantic score\
- aircraft affinity boost\
- role relevance boost\
- frequent-doc-type boost\
- recent-tail-number boost\
- task-intent boost\
- permission applicability boost\
\
But ensure:\
- grounded document hits still win\
- behavior only boosts ranking, not truth\
- user can always override and search globally\
\
